Substack Notes has been around for two and a half years now, and the feed i=
s beginning to resemble a thriving jungle=E2=80=94alive with fascinating cr=
eatures who each play a vital role in the ecosystem, helping one another gr=
ow and evolve.
To celebrate everything that=E2=80=99s blooming on Notes, we=E2=80=99ve put=
 together a little field guide to the many species of posters you=E2=80=99l=
l encounter. This isn=E2=80=99t meant to be comprehensive; think of it as a=
 snapshot of the landscape, with a focus on art, culture, and humor=E2=80=
=94the subjects we suspect most readers of The Substack Post find irresisti=
ble.
The Shitposters Satirical Social Commentators
In a since-deleted note, anonymous poster LL  asked her followers to stop r=
eferring to her as a shitposter. Whatever you call LL and her contemporarie=
s, every good place on the internet needs them.
father_karine  blesses our feed with a mix of lighthearted humor and biting=
 criticism.
Fashion investigator Biz Sherbert  is believably optimistic about all sorts=
 of things.
Dia Lupo  (yes, it=E2=80=99s her real name; no relation to Dua Lipa) fires =
off observational missives about her life and times.
See also: donald boat [ https://substack.com/@donaldboat ], harry [ https:/=
/substack.com/@lexaprotools ], Shaiyan [ https://substack.com/@shaiyan ], c=
aleb hearon [ https://substack.com/@calebsaysthings ], evanie laurent [ htt=
ps://substack.com/@evanielaurent ], tom [ https://substack.com/@hmpshr? ], =
danielle [ https://substack.com/@rawandferal? ], Mackenzie Thomas [ https:/=
/substack.com/@iwilldowhateveriwant ], M.E. Rothwell [ https://substack.com=
/@merothwell ], Philip Traylen [ https://substack.com/@oldoldoldoldnew? ], =
Paul Staples [ https://substack.com/@paulstaples ], Emma Newman-Holden [ ht=
tps://substack.com/@myvapeisdying ], ziwe =20
The Tumblr Diaspora
These posters bring the ~aesthetic~ energy to Notes. They make excellent us=
e of the photo gallery feature, devising clever themes around beautiful ima=
ges.
Alex DiCapo Patel  frequently shares photos from runway shows past.
stephanie  collects photos of =E2=80=9Cliving women artists you should know=
=2E=E2=80=9D
Zo=C3=AB Yasemin  shares old and new editorial campaigns from fashion magaz=
ines and advertisements.
See also: Rose Florence [ https://substack.com/@roseflorence ], Elsie Moral=
es [ https://substack.com/@cazadora?utm_source=3Dglobal-search ], surrealis=
t covens [ https://substack.com/@surrealistcovens?utm_source=3Dglobal-searc=
h ], Lauren Sands [ https://substack.com/@laurensands?utm_source=3Dglobal-s=
earch ], Kate McBride [ https://substack.com/@poutdracula?utm_source=3Dglob=
al-search ], LoLo [ https://substack.com/@lovehistories?utm_source=3Dglobal=
-search ], Nick Struutinsky [ https://substack.com/@nicksobek?utm_source=3D=
global-search ], Kayla Roolart [ https://substack.com/@kaylaroolaart?r=3Dsv=
fe&utm_medium=3Dios&utm_source=3Dprofile ], Alana Fallon [ https://substack=
=2Ecom/@alanafallon ], Gabriella Karefa=
-Johnson [ https://substack.com/@gabri=
ellakarefajohnson?utm_source=3Dsubstack-feed-item&utm_content=3Dc-169545294=
 ]
The Literary Crowd
There are a ton of readers and writers on Substack, but these posters are t=
he ones building a new literary scene. They=E2=80=99re starting magazines, =
sharing thoughts on literary gossip du jour, hyping other writers=E2=80=99 =
work; in other words, they=E2=80=99re turning Substack into a modern-day li=
terary salon.
When Celine Nguyen  isn=E2=80=99t writing an ode to Proust or a modern hist=
ory of AI, she=E2=80=99s closely reading other writers on Substack and shar=
ing their work with thoughtful recommendations.
As the editor of The Metropolitan Review, Ross Barkan  has played a key rol=
e in showcasing the literary bona fides of Substackers.
A generous reader and writer, Naomi Kanakia  recommends the Great Books and=
 great posts with equal verve.
See also: Alexander Sorondo [ https://substack.com/@alexandersorondo ], Sam=
 Kahn [ https://substack.com/@samkahn ], Henry Begler [ https://substack.co=
m/@agoodhardstare ]
The Young and Newyorkish
These are the journalists who live in New York and either write for mainstr=
eam media outlets or used to write for them. Ignore Hamish=E2=80=99s shade=
=E2=80=94they keep us apprised of what=E2=80=99s happening, share updates o=
n the media scandals of the day, and, yes, let us know what=E2=80=99s cool.
Emily Sundberg  asks the hard questions.
Teddy (T.M.) Brown  weighs in on the latest media industry gossip making th=
e rounds.
Kaitlin Phillips  has joined the dark side.
See also: Danya Issawi [ https://substack.com/@danyaissawi ], Delia Cai [ h=
ttps://substack.com/@deliacai ], J Wortham [ https://substack.com/@jennydel=
uxe ], Chris Gayomali [ https://substack.com/@chrisgayomali? ], Mary H.K. C=
hoi [ https://substack.com/@maryhkchoi ], Rachel Seville Tashjian [ https:/=
/substack.com/@rstrstrst? ], JP Brammer [ https://substack.com/@johnpaulbra=
mmer ], Molly Young =20
The Artists
It turns out that some of you can paint, sketch, design, knit, sew, and do =
all other manner of art-making.
Gabe  illustrates the everyday.
Kika MacFarlane  is always creating something.
Ella Emhoff  is knitting up a storm.
See also: Erika Lee Sears [ https://substack.com/@erikaleesears?utm_source=
=3Dglobal-search ], Manu Montoya [ https://substack.com/@manumontoya? ], As=
her Perlman [ https://substack.com/@asherperlman ], Liana Finck [ https://s=
ubstack.com/@lianafinck ], Jason Chatfield [ https://substack.com/@jasoncha=
tfield ], Eliza Brooke [ https://substack.com/@elizabrooke ], Tala Rae Schl=
ossberg [ https://substack.com/@talaraeschlossberg ], Harry Stooshinoff [ h=
ttps://substack.com/@harrystooshinoff? ], Janet Asante Sullivan [ https://s=
ubstack.com/@janetasantesullivan? ]
Pamela Anderson
Did you know Pamela Anderson  is on Substack?
The Memelords
I don=E2=80=99t know if they make the memes themselves. I don=E2=80=99t car=
e. We need more memes on Substack. Thank you to these posters.
Vanya Bagaev =20
Leonard Morton =20
ryu =20
The Cats
This is still God=E2=80=99s internet after all.
Tao Lin  gets inside Nini=E2=80=99s mind.
Santi Ara=C3=BAjo  shares an endlessly amusing stream of found cat photos.
soleil  is a cat seemingly posting photos of =E2=80=A6 herself?
Have a favorite Notes poster? Let us know in the comments.

